# C++ Style Directives

1. Use smart pointers with custom deleters for FFmpeg resources:
   ```cpp
   using FormatContextPtr = std::unique_ptr<AVFormatContext, AVFormatContextDeleter>;
   FormatContextPtr formatContext(formatContextRaw);
   ```

2. Log verbosely with class name prefixes:
   ```cpp
   std::cout << "[AsyncKeyframesWorker] Processing URL: " << url_ << std::endl;
   ```

3. Handle errors early with detailed messages:
   ```cpp
   if (openResult != 0) {
     char errBuf[AV_ERROR_MAX_STRING_SIZE];
     av_strerror(openResult, errBuf, AV_ERROR_MAX_STRING_SIZE);
     SetError("Failed to open input file: " + std::string(errBuf));
     return;
   }
   ```

4. Use promise-based async patterns for Node.js addons:
   ```cpp
   auto deferred = Napi::Promise::Deferred::New(env);
   AsyncKeyframesWorker *worker = new AsyncKeyframesWorker(url, deferred);
   worker->Queue();
   return deferred.Promise();
   ```

5. Check parameters rigorously:
   ```cpp
   if (info.Length() < 1 || !info[0].IsString()) {
     Napi::TypeError::New(env, "URL expected as first argument").ThrowAsJavaScriptException();
     return env.Null();
   }
   ```

6. Separate execution from result handling in async workers:
   ```cpp
   void Execute() { /* work logic */ }
   void OnOK() { /* success handling */ }
   void OnError(const Napi::Error &error) { /* error handling */ }
   ```

7. Use native STL containers for collections:
   ```cpp
   std::vector<Keyframe> keyframes_;
   ```

8. Always log messages to stderr, stdout is exclusively for program data output. stderr doesn't imply failure
